    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 3-level hierarchical structure with 6 nodes and 6 links. Categorical variables define the taxonomic relationships between abstract data measurement concepts. Node colors (#F2CFE2 for categorical subtypes, #E1F3CF for continuous subtypes) create immediate visual categorization. The inverted layout optimizes horizontal space utilization while maintaining parent-child directional clarity through vertical connectors. The organization chart type maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating gridlines and using minimal connector lines. Color contrast between level 0 (blue tint) and child nodes (pink/green tints) applies Cairo's principle of perceptual grouping. Node spacing and uniform width (65px) maintain rhythmic visual patterns that aid pattern recognition in hierarchical data visualization."
